  <div class="pi"><span class="ic">🐶</span><div><div class="label">Pet Friendly</div><div class="sub">Dogs welcome</div></div></div>
  <div class="pi"><span class="ic">📅</span><div><div class="label">Weekly &amp; Monthly</div><div class="sub">Extended stay rates</div></div></div>
  <div class="pi"><span class="ic">🚛</span><div><div class="label">Truck Parking</div><div class="sub">Work vehicles welcome</div></div></div>
</div>

<div class="content-wrap">

  <div class="intro-pull rv">
    Naples, Utah is a small city in Uintah County sitting directly adjacent to Vernal — they share a border and for most practical purposes operate as a single community. If you're visiting Naples, working in Naples, or passing through the area, <strong>Best Western Vernal Inn</strong> is your closest full-service lodging option, just a short drive away with full amenities, comfortable rooms, and rates for every length of stay.
  </div>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>Naples and Vernal — Two Cities, One Community</h2>
    <p>Naples (population ~6,000) and Vernal (population ~10,000) sit side by side in the Uintah Basin, separated by a city limit line that most residents and visitors barely notice. The two cities share US-40, the main commercial corridor, utility infrastructure, and the same access to the surrounding recreation areas and energy industry.</p>
    <p>For hotel guests, the practical reality is simple: there is no full-service hotel in Naples itself. Best Western Vernal Inn is the closest quality lodging option, and the drive between the two cities is a matter of minutes.</p>
    <div class="pro-tip">
      <p><strong>Local note:</strong> If you're searching for a "Naples Utah hotel" and coming up short, that's why. Vernal is where the hotels are — and we're the closest and most complete option to the Naples area.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>Who Stays With Us From Naples</h2>
    <div class="highlight-cards">
      <div class="hcard">
        <div class="hc-icon">🔧</div>
        <strong>Contractors &amp; Tradespeople</strong>
