        <div class="inc-item">Free high-speed Wi-Fi</div>
        <div class="inc-item">In-room microwave</div>
        <div class="inc-item">In-room refrigerator</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Flat-screen TV</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Desk &amp; work area</div>
        <div class="inc-item">On-site laundry</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Truck &amp; trailer parking</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Pet-friendly rooms available</div>
        <div class="inc-item">Best Western Rewards points</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section rv">
    <h2>Explore the Area Around Naples &amp; Vernal</h2>
    <p>The Naples–Vernal area is surrounded by some of the most striking outdoor recreation in the American West. Whether you're here for work or play, these destinations are all within easy reach.</p>
    <div class="attraction-cards">
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>🦕 Dinosaur National Monument</strong>
        <p>~20 minutes from Vernal. World-famous fossil quarry, canyon scenic drives, petroglyphs, and river corridors along the Green and Yampa Rivers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>🎣 Flaming Gorge</strong>
        <p>~40 minutes. World-class fishing, boating, and the dramatic Red Canyon overlook above the reservoir. One of Utah's great scenic drives.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>🏊 Red Fleet State Park</strong>
        <p>~15 minutes. Swimming, kayaking, dinosaur trackway, and beautiful red-rock reservoir scenery just north of Vernal.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>🏛️ Utah Field House</strong>
        <p>Right in downtown Vernal. Natural history museum with full-scale dinosaur exhibits — great for families and a perfect rainy-day option.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>⛰️ Uinta Mountains</strong>
        <p>~1 hour. The highest range in Utah, with high-alpine lakes, fishing, and wilderness hiking accessible from the Ashley National Forest trailheads.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="attr-card">
        <strong>🪨 Steinaker State Park</strong>
        <p>~10 minutes north of Vernal. Water skiing, fishing, and camping on a quiet reservoir with easy access from US-191.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

